extensionDescription.message: Move, sort, and copy videos in your playlists faster and easier.

hint101.message: You can enable and disable multiple selection with the blue icon button in the header bar

hint101a.message: If multiple selection is disabled, key bindings are also disabled

hint102.message: If you navigate to another page, the current selection is lost

hint103.message: If you continue navigating in the same direction in a menu or on a page, you go from first to last and from last to first item

hint104.message: “Watch more” and “Show less” in the left pane with playlist names can be expanded and collapsed with Ctrl+I

hint105.message: In this version, the clipboard is a small memory within the extension and not the operating system clipboard

hint106.message: The theme (dark/light) is automatically adopted from YouTube™

hint201.message: You can select or deselect a video with a mouse click

hint202.message: You can select or deselect a focused video with Spacebar/Enter

hint203.message: A focused video has a turquoise border

hint203a.message: If you don't see a focus or no video has been focused yet, press a navigation key

hint204.message: A selected video will be highlighted in steel blue and will have a check mark in the bottom right corner

hint205.message: Hold down the Shift key to select multiple consecutive videos

hint205a.message: Click or focus on the first video to select, hold Shift and click or focus on the last video to select

hint206.message: You can select videos with the filter

hint207.message: You can save the IDs of the selected videos to a file

hint301.message: You can only add videos to your own playlists, including Watch later

hint302.message: You can only delete videos in your own playlists, including Watch later, Liked videos, and History

hint302a.message: Videos are only deleted if you confirm the security prompt

hint303.message: Videos are added to the top or bottom of a playlist as configured in the playlist settings

hint304.message: You can add videos from a file

kbCopySelectedVideos.message: Copies the selected videos to the clipboard

kbCutSelectedVideos.message: Copies the selected videos to the clipboard and deletes them from your playlist or history (with security prompt)

kbDeleteSelectedVideos.message: Deletes the selected videos or the focused video from your playlist or history (with confirmation prompt)

kbFocusLastVideo.message: Focuses the last video (loads the next batch of videos)

kbPasteVideos.message: Pastes the videos from the clipboard into the current playlist

kbToggleFocusedVideo.message: Selects or deselects the focused video
